====================================================================
PROJECT CONTEXT & STATE - v1.9 (PoC Complete)
Date: February 13, 2026
Team: Jim (AI) & Partner (Human)
====================================================================

1. PROJECT STATUS: READY FOR TESTING
- The "Fast Model" Proof of Concept is feature-complete.
- It is a standalone, client-side web application (HTML/CSS/JS).
- No server or database is required for this phase.

2. KEY FEATURES DELIVERED
- Visual Interface: "Zone-Based" SVG Mannequin (Front/Back).
- Logic: Dual-State Tracking (Red = Pain, Green = Treated).
- Input: "Chip" buttons for rapid selection of Technique/Response.
- Output Engine: 
  - Real-time SOAP Text generation.
  - Automated PDF "Superbill/Record" generation (Client-side).
  - CSV Data Export.
- Persistence: Auto-saves to LocalStorage; "New Session" resets.
- Customization: "Therapist Voice" settings modal.

3. ARCHITECTURE DECISIONS
- Chosen "Global Settings" for Technique/Response (Speed over Granularity).
- Chosen "Client-Side PDF" (jspdf) to ensure privacy and offline capability.
- Chosen "Mobile Stack" CSS to allow use on phones/tablets.

4. NEXT STEPS (Post-PoC)
- Deploy to GitHub Pages.
- Field Test: Therapist uses it for 1 day in the clinic.
- Feedback Loop: Does "Global Settings" cover 90% of cases?
====================================================================

====================================================================
PROJECT CONTEXT: MFR RAPID DOCUMENTATION TOOL
Version: 2.2 (The "Humanoid" Golden Master)
Date: February 13, 2026
Team: Jim (AI) & Partner
Status: SHIPPED / PoC COMPLETE
====================================================================

1. THE MISSION
Create a frictionless, client-side documentation tool for Manual Therapists 
that generates CPT 97140 billing data and SOAP notes in under 30 seconds.

2. FINAL TECH STACK
- Core: HTML5, CSS3, Vanilla JavaScript (ES6+).
- Libraries: jsPDF (v2.5.1 via CDN) for client-side PDF generation.
- Data Storage: LocalStorage (Browser-based persistence).
- Hosting: Ready for GitHub Pages (Static Site).

3. KEY FEATURES DELIVERED
A. The Visual Interface
   - Custom SVG Mannequin: Organic, "Humanoid" zones (V2.1).
   - Granularity: Digits, Joints (Shoulder/Knee/Ankle), Spine Regions.
   - Dual-State Logic: Red (Pain) vs. Green (Treated).

B. The "Engine"
   - Chip Buttons: Single-tap selection for Technique & Response.
   - Smart Text: Auto-generates SOAP narrative based on selections.
   - PDF Generator: Creates a dual-purpose "Superbill + Chart Note" PDF.
   - CSV Export: For raw data backup.

C. User Experience
   - Mobile Stack: Auto-detects phones and adjusts layout for thumbs.
   - Therapist Voice: Settings modal to customize default phrases.
   - Safety Net: Auto-saves on every click; "New Session" resets.

4. FILE MANIFEST (V2.2)
- index.html: Contains the V2.1 Organic SVG and V1.9 Logic wiring.
- styles.css: Contains the Chip styling, Mobile Media Queries, and Layout.
- app.js: Contains the PDF logic, State Management, and Settings logic.

5. FUTURE ROADMAP (V3.0 - The SaaS Pivot)
- [BACKLOG] User Authentication (Supabase/Firebase).
- [BACKLOG] Cloud Database (Sync across devices).
- [BACKLOG] Multi-Patient Management (Save/Load specific profiles).
- [BACKLOG] Dark Mode.

6. KNOWN CONSTRAINTS
- "Global Settings": Technique/Response applies to the whole session (Speed tradeoff).
- Browser Dependency: Clearing browser cache wipes the "Therapist Voice" settings.
====================================================================
